      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an aging Labrador, a balanced diet is key, but the ideal protein-to-fat ratio can vary based on specific health needs. Generally, look for food with high-quality, easily digestible protein sources paired with moderate, healthy fats. Since your lab is older, focusing on nutrient density and joint support is often as important as the exact ratio itself. It's always best to consult your veterinarian to tailor a specific recommendation for your dog's individual health profile.",
