    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you should definitely consider caloric density when your Labrador's activity levels have decreased. To maintain muscle mass without gaining weight, you want a food that is calorically dense in nutrients but controlled in overall calories. Look for foods formulated for \"Senior\" or \"Weight Management\" as they are designed to be more digestible and less calorie-dense for less active seniors. This helps you meet his protein needs without excess energy intake.",
